    <div class="container" style="max-width:800px;">
        <h1 style="font-size:1.8rem;font-weight:800;margin-bottom:4px;">About FightingData</h1>
        <p style="color:#777;font-size:15px;margin-bottom:32px;">The story behind the data.</p>
        
        <div class="card" style="padding:24px;margin-bottom:20px;">
            <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem;font-weight:800;margin-bottom:12px;padding-bottom:8px;border-bottom:2px solid #111;">What We Do</h2>
            <p style="color:#555;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px;">
                FightingData.com is a UFC analytics platform built for people who want to understand matchups through data, not hot takes. Every time a fight card is announced, we generate head-to-head statistical breakdowns for every matchup on the card — striking, grappling, control, finishing tendencies — so you can form your own opinions grounded in real numbers.
            </p>
            <p style="color:#555;line-height:1.7;">
                We don't sell picks. We don't predict winners. We present the data clearly and let you draw your own conclusions.
            </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card" style="padding:24px;margin-bottom:20px;">
            <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem;font-weight:800;margin-bottom:12px;padding-bottom:8px;border-bottom:2px solid #111;">How It Works</h2>
            <p style="color:#555;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px;">
                When you open a fighter comparison, you'll see two tables: career statistics and recent performance. Career stats cover every UFC fight a fighter has had since November 2000. Recent performance focuses on their most recent bouts to capture current form — because a fighter's last few outings often tell a different story than their career averages.
            </p>
            <p style="color:#555;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:12px;">
                Edge indicators highlight which fighter has the statistical advantage in each category. These aren't predictions — they're a quick visual guide to where each fighter's strengths and vulnerabilities lie relative to their opponent.
            </p>
            <p style="color:#555;line-height:1.7;">
                We break analysis into three areas: <strong>striking</strong> (accuracy, volume, defense, knockdowns), <strong>grappling</strong> (takedown accuracy vs. opponent's takedown defense, submission attempts, control time), and <strong>finishing ability</strong> (KO rate, submission rate, and how fights typically end).
            </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card" style="padding:24px;margin-bottom:20px;">
            <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem;font-weight:800;margin-bottom:12px;padding-bottom:8px;border-bottom:2px solid #111;">Our Data</h2>
            <p style="color:#555;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:16px;">
                All fight statistics are sourced from <a href="http://ufcstats.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">UFCStats.com</a>, the official statistics provider for the UFC. We verify accuracy through automated validation checks and manual spot-checks against the source.
            </p>
